  "text": "The harmonics amplitude of load voltage error can be expressed by (10) , leading to the harmonic spectrum depicted in Fig. 6 (black column at left side). In the same figure are shown the corresponding values obtained by circuit simulation with different modulation indexes (m = 0.1, 0.2, 0.45, columns from left to right side). Note that the amplitude of fundamental U 1 is calculated according to [CITATION_1] . In Fig. 6 (a) is considered the case of load power factor PF = 1, whereas in Fig. 6 (b) is considered the case of load power factor PF = -1.",
